<doc id="450353" wikidata="Q5599483" url="?curid=450353" title="Great Lakes Storm">
<text>The Great Lakes Storm was a basketball team that played in the Continental Basketball Association (CBA) for three seasons, beginning in 2002 and ending in 2005. They were based in Birch Run, Michigan, a small town between Flint and Saginaw. The Storm played at the Birch Run Expo Center. The original team was called the Flint Fuze.

